6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 999, L.D. 1515, “An Act to Exempt
10 Wheelchair Adapted Vehicles from the Sales and Use Tax”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Exempt Wheelchair Adapted Motor Vehicles from the Sales and Use Tax'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
14 following:
15 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §1760, sub-§96 is enacted to read:
16 96. Wheelchair adapted motor vehicles. Beginning January 1, 2026, sales of motor
17 vehicles adapted to accommodate a wheelchair actively occupied by an individual while
18 the motor vehicle is operated from the wheelchair or by another occupant of the motor
19 vehicle and motor vehicles for which the owner attests such modifications are necessary
20 and will be completed within 6 months of the motor vehicle's purchase.
21 As used in this subsection, "adapted to accommodate a wheelchair" means equipped with
22 altered controls or a mechanical lifting device designed to accommodate a wheelchair.
23 In order to obtain the exemption provided in this subsection, the purchaser must possess an
24 unexpired disability registration plate or placard issued pursuant to Title 29-A, section 521.'
25 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
26 number to read consecutively.
27 SUMMARY
2288 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment exempts from
2299 the sales and use tax sales of motor vehicles adapted for the use of occupants in wheelchairs
3300 or intended to be so adapted within 6 months of purchase. Purchasers must possess an
3311 active disability registration plate or placard in order to obtain the exemption.
